videos.description: A'ja Wilson shows off her athleticism with a slick spin move to set up a layup finish.
videos.headline: Wilson's slick spin move sets up scoop layup finish

videos.description: Victoria Vivians finishes the fast break with a nice and-1 layup.
videos.headline: Vivians finishes break with and-1

videos.description: South Carolina head coach Dawn Staley talks about wanting her team to be more patient to prevent fast break buckets for the opposition.
videos.headline: Staley wants more patience from her team

videos.description: A'ja wilson finishes her drive with the hoop and the harm.
videos.headline: Wilson fired up after and-1 finish

videos.description: A'ja Wilson and South Carolina celebrate the Gamecocks' SEC Tournament Championship win.
videos.headline: South Carolina celebrates SEC Tournament win

videos.description: South Carolina's Kaela Davis talks about the atmosphere and excitement after winning the SEC Tournament.
videos.headline: Davis 'living the dream' after winning championship

videos.description: South Carolina coach Dawn Staley discusses winning the 2017 SEC Tournament.
videos.headline: Staley talks Gamecocks' third straight SEC championship

videos.description: SEC commissioner Greg Sankey presents South Carolina with the SEC Tournament Championship trophy.
videos.headline: South Carolina receives championship trophy

videos.description: No. 5 South Carolina outlasts No. 6 Mississippi State 59-49 to win its third straight SEC title.
